          <h2 class="title">JPEG2000 Virtual Slide microscope</h2>
            <!-- START main content -->
            
<div id="node-1" class="node clear-block">
      <div class="content"><p>This website presents our research group's work in the field of digital pathology and <a href="?q=virtual_microscopy">virtual microscopy</a>. Our group has developed <a href="?q=jpeg2000_and_jpip">JPEG2000</a>- and <a href="?q=jpeg2000_and_jpip">JPEG2000 Interactive Protocol</a> (JPIP) -based software consisting of image compression, viewing, and network server applications, all suited for the needs of virtual microscopy. We have also released software for linking virtual slides with the <a href="?q=dicom_and_virtual_microscopy">Digital Imaging and Communications in Medicine</a> (DICOM) standard by using JPIP. Our latest research project describes a web application (<a href="http://jvsmicroscope.uta.fi/immunoratio/">ImmunoRatio</a>) for quantitative image analysis of hormone receptor and Ki-67 immunostained breast cancer slides.</p>
<p>All our software is freely <a href="?q=software">downloadable</a> and usable, and can be tested using <a href="?q=virtual_slides">the virtual slide examples</a> located in our public servers.</p>
<p><strong>Recent additions</strong></p>
<p><table cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" border="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><span style="color: rgb(128, 0, 0);"><strong>4.11.2010</strong></span></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><a href="../../../../../../immunomembrane/">ImmunoMembrane web application</a> for analyzing HER-2 cell membrane immunostains opened for public use</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><span style="color: rgb(128, 0, 0);"><strong>3.8.2010</strong></span></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><a href="http://breast-cancer-research.com/content/12/4/R56">ImmunoRatio journal article</a> published</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><span style="color: rgb(128, 0, 0);"><strong>1.8.2010</strong></span></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><a href="http://jvsmicroscope.uta.fi/?q=presentations">Presentations</a> from the 10th European Congress on Telepathology and 4th International Congress on Virtual Microscopy (Vilnius, Lithuania) added</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><span style="color: rgb(128, 0, 0);"><strong>24.5.2010</strong></span></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><a href="/?q=skeleton_intersections">Skeleton Intersections plugin</a> published</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="color: rgb(128, 0, 0);"><strong>9.3.2010</strong></span></td>
